It was a matter of minutes before the internet was overloaded with viral images mocking Brazil for their 7-1 defeat to Germany.

Christ the Redeemer, the iconic statue of Jesus Christ in Rio de Janeiro, is normally seen as an image of hope - but the famous landmark was quickly photo-shopped at the expense of the defeated host nation, following their semi-final humiliation.

Today Twitter revealed that Brazil's humiliating loss in the semi-final was the most talked about individual sports game ever on the social network with users sending 5.6 million tweets during the game.

